[SN]TITLE[SN]
Boy in hospital after being hit by car in Glasgow

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 10-year-old boy has been taken to hospital after being hit by a car in Glasgow on Saturday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The boy was struck on Dalmarnock Road at about 15:10.
He has been taken to Queen Elizabeth University Hospital. There is no update on his condition.
The road was closed between Dunn Street and Muslin Street for an accident investigation to be carried out.
